  "commentaries": {
    "sayana": {
      "rishi": "Nārada",
      "chandas": "Anuṣṭup",
      "devata": "Śambhu",
      "sanskrit": "",
      "english": "'Prataranah'—the cause of crossing over (tarana) sins through excellent (prakrishta) means like mantra-chanting. 'Uttaranah'—the cause of crossing out of (uttarana) this worldly existence through the form of essential knowledge (tattva-jnana). (14)"
    },
    "bhatta_bhaskara": {
      "rishi": "Nārada",
      "chandas": "Anuṣṭup",
      "devata": "Śambhu",
      "sanskrit": "",
      "english": "'Namah prataranaya cha'. 'Taranam' is living or crossing. Excellence is birth in higher wombs. [Grammatical note]. He is the means for crossing over Samsara. To the cause of crossing over with excellence in this world. 'Uttaranaya cha'—to the cause of crossing out of (exiting) this world. [Grammatical note]. (14)"
    },
